  "prompt": "Are grapes bad for any breeds of dogs?",
  "response": "Yes, grapes and raisins can be toxic to dogs, though the exact reason for this toxicity is not fully understood. Certain breeds may be more susceptible, but there is no definitive list of breeds that are safe or unsafe. Some dogs may experience kidney failure after ingesting grapes or raisins, while others may not show any symptoms even after consuming them. Because of this unpredictability, it's best to keep grapes and raisins away from all dogs. If a dog does consume grapes or raisins, it\u2019s important to contact a veterinarian immediately for advice.",
